The paper deals with parameterized counting problems, which are often studied in the computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of combined matchgates and the study of structural parameters of graphs suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.GT).
